property.Title: Dowding Road, Westerham, TN16
property.Description:
DESIRABLE, superb and substantial are just three out of many words that can be used to describe this ATTRACTIVE 4 bedroom SEMI-DETACHED family home that offers approximately 1949 SQ.FT of fabulousness, situated in a very popular cul-de-sac on Biggin Hill Top. Downstairs this lovely home comprises of three large open plan rooms used as dining room, living room and family room, a separate kitchen, utility, cloakroom, front porch, garage and gym. Upstairs you will find four double bedrooms, all of which have built-in storage, the master bedroom also benefits from an en suite shower room and there is a separate family bathroom. Externally this property will satisfy just as much as it does inside with a large beautiful flat lawn and patio area. To the front there is an in/out drive providing ample off-road parking.

A substantial extended four bedroom property in a favourable cul de sac at the top of Biggin Hill. Downstairs this lovely family home comprises three large open plan reception rooms, the lounge has double door opening onto the family room and dining room and doors leading to a great covered seating area, perfect for entertaining and summer barbeques. A modern kitchen/breakfast room and a handy separate utility room and downstairs cloakroom. An enclosed covered pathway leads to a home office space or study and a room currently used as a TV room or formally part of the garage. Upstairs you will find four double bedrooms, all of which have built-in storage, master bedroom with ensuite and a separate family bathroom. Externally there is a large level garden mainly laid to lawn with a shed and a summer house, to the front plenty of off street parking for several cars on the driveway.

Biggin Hill has the advantage of being surrounded by Green Belt countryside and yet is only 7.5 miles from Bromley's main shopping centre and railway station which offers a regular service into London. Croydon can also be accessed via bus to New Addington then Tramlink to Croydon. Access to the M25 motorway is approx. 7.5 miles away. Biggin Hill also benefits from a Waitrose Supermarket, and a library and swimming pool complex. Local schools include Oaklands Infants and Juniors, Biggin Hill Primary and Charles Darwin Academy. Historically Biggin Hill Airport played an important role as an RAF Fighter Station during WWII. The RAF Chapel is still in use and can be found by the popular landmark Spitfire and Hurricane.
